<br>
IMO, Ogres are loaded up to be better SK's - their stat sum is something like 27 points higher than Trolls, and, as I recall (I agonized over this decision too - whether to go ogre or troll with an SK twink, but it was so long ago) ogres spread them out better for SK's.<br>
<br>
Slam _is_ nice, especially for SK's who don't even get stuns - it gives you at least a chance to stop the otherwise inevitable.  I would play a large race for certain if I was playing a SK.  And between the two large races, then stun resistance of ogres <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> seems</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be a huge benefit.<br>
<br>
But I have to be honest:  I don't know exactly how it works.  Could an Ogre enlighten me please?  Can you honestly <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> not</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> be melee stunned by a mob that you're facing?  If this is so, then the choice is clear.  Some troll SK's may benefit from the minor regen bonus, since I understand SK soloing is generally not a heavy tank activity, and you should be able to slowly recharge your HP and be okay, but honestly, the difference is menial if you just slap on a fungi tunic.<br>
<br>
I chose ogre.<br>
<br>
From an RP perspective:<br>
<br>
Go with the race that you most <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> want</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to be.  If it's your twink, it should be fun, fun, fun.  Gameplay shouldn't guide that decision so delicately as to dictate which race you must choose.  That's why I scrapped my Iksar warrior at level 12 and went with a wood elf!  I realized that that was what I wanted to be.  My twink will never surpass my main for a raiding role anyway.<br>
<br>
When I chose Ogre over Troll, I was happy with the decision because I wanted my character to be gigantic and stupid as a rock and mildly yucky, but all in an adorable sort of way - his entire raison d'etre, it turned out, was to rescue eggs from snakes and put them in the bank and wait for them to hatch into little ogres.  <br>
<br>
Granted, trolls in general make the biggest riot on EQ, but I'm not quite cut out to bathe in filth and be one.  And at that, my one or two favourite fattties are actually Ogres.  Either fatty can put on a good show.<br>
<br>
From an uberosity perspective, my gut says Ogre (others may disagree - I never played an SK to high level, so listen to them), but if this is your twink, you <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> have</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> to make the decision that makes you have the most fun - not the most stats (unless most fun = most stats for you, which is also okay - especially if you want to make your twink especially uber).<br>
<br>
IMO, Twinks should put a silly grin on your face.  Playing them should be like a vacation =)<br>
